<paragraph id="8B8118792F04FFBE02E2FCF1E1932A71" blockId="105.[189,1399,831,1069]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicName id="4C3E63FA2F04FFBE02E2FCF1E1982D05" authorityName="C. B. Clarke" authorityYear="1879" box="[189,402,831,857]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="khasiana">
<emphasis id="B94AC46B2F04FFBE02E2FCF1E1982D05" box="[189,402,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Begonia khasiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from its 
<typeStatus id="5485A6DB2F04FFBE00ECFCF1E2EC2D06" box="[691,742,832,858]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
collection from Sillet (Clarke mentions both Sillet and Khasia in the protologue) or HBC (Hortus Botanic Calcutta) the specimen actually has both on it. The plants at first glance resemble 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E63FA2F04FFBE0077FC37E2D42DC3" authorityName="Wall. (Wallich" authorityYear="1830" box="[552,734,901,927]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pedunculosa">
<emphasis id="B94AC46B2F04FFBE0077FC37E2D42DC3" box="[552,734,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">B. pedunculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differ by having more membranous leaves, axillary inflorescences that do not branch as much and much smaller flowers and fruit, and the male flowers seemingly have only two tepals. Clarke published the species under â€˜doubtful and excluded speciesâ€™ as without more specimens to clarify the species the specimens could pass as an impoverished specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E63FA2F04FFBE0282FBA2E19B2A70" authorityName="Wall. (Wallich" authorityYear="1830" box="[221,401,1042,1068]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pedunculosa">
<emphasis id="B94AC46B2F04FFBE0282FBA2E19B2A70" box="[221,401,1042,1068]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">B. pedunculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
